            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>ἔζησεν Μαρτίριος ἔτη εἴκοσι δύω
                    <lb n="2"/>εἰρήνη σοι <expan><abbr><am><g ref="#christogram">☧</g></am></abbr><ex>Χριστό</ex><abbr>ς</abbr></expan>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text after De Amico and Kaibel</note></app>
                    <app><note>As Kaibel notes, De Amico places interpuncts between each word, but given the confusion around the numeral at the end of line 1, these seem unlikely to have been present on the original</note></app>
                    <app loc="1"><note>Kaibel: Μαρτ[ύ]ριος; De Amico: ΕΙΚΟΣΙΑ.ΥΩ, reasonably interpreted by Kaibel as a misreading of ΔΥΩ</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Martirios lived 22 years. Peace upon you. Christos</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p></p>
            </div>
